3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with communication and networking, specifically in the context of network-constrained averaging. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm for network-constrained averaging, which falls under the umbrella of distributed computing.
